events.name: New York Knicks at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 19 of his season-high 35 points in the third quarter, Pascal Siakam had 20 points and 14 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors extended their home winning streak against the Knicks to 11 games by beating a depleted New York team...
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet scores season-high 35, Raptors rout Knicks 120-105

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored a career-high 50 points, rallying the Boston Celtics from 14 points down late in the fourth quarter to a 116-111 overtime victory over the Orlando Magic on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 50, rallies Celts to 116-111 OT win over Magic

headlines.description: — Rookie Evan Mobley had 24 points and nine rebounds, Kevin Love scored 20 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers snapped a three-game losing streak with a 108-104 win over the Indiana Pacers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mobley, Love help Cavaliers rally past Pacers 108-104

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 24 points, Jalen Smith tied a career high with 19 points and 12 rebounds and the short-handed Phoenix Suns hammered the Charlotte Hornets 133-99 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 24 points, depleted Suns rout Hornets 133-99

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: - Luka Doncic had 14 points, 10 assists and nine rebounds in his return from a 10-game absence and Marquese Chriss came off the bench to score a season-high 15 points, leading the Dallas Mavericks to a 95-86 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Sunday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs win; Thunder's Giddey youngest to post triple-double

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 26 points, Malik Monk added 22 and the Los Angeles Lakers hung on to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 108-103 on Sunday night for the first time in three meetings this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: James, Monk help Lakers edge Timberwolves 108-103
